jerked herself away. Do you know what she 
said to me ? She said, My confidence has gone 
forever. " 

" I did n t know she was such a prig ! " Sher 
ringham exclaimed. "They re queer people, 
verily, with water in their veins instead of blood. 
You and I would n t be like that, should we ? 



, $2$ 

though you have taken up such a discouraging 
position, about caring for a fellow." 

" I care for art," poor Biddy returned. 

" You do, to some purpose," said Peter, glan 
cing at the bust. 

" To that of making you laugh at me." 

" Would you give a good man up for that ? " 

" A good man ? What man ? " 

"Well, say me if I wanted to marry you." 

Biddy hesitated a little. " Of course I would, 
in a moment. At any rate, I d give up the 
