you, nor me either ! " 

" He can t hurt me, my dear, and neither can 
you ; for I have a nice little heart of stone and a 
smart new breastplate of iron. The interest I 
take in you is something quite extraordinary ; 



 68 1 

but the most extraordinary thing in it is that it s 
perfectly prepared to tolerate the interest of 
others." 

" The interest of others need n t trouble it 
much ! " Miriam declared. " If Mr. Dormer has 
broken off his marriage to such an awfully fine 
woman (for she is that, your swell of a sister), it 
isn t fora loud wretch like me. He s kind to 
