neither you nor me any good ! " 

He paused a moment, upon which Miriam 
asked, " That I do know what ? " 

"That I have a consuming passion for you and 
that it s impossible." 

" Ah, impossible, my friend ! " she sighed, but 
with a quickness in her assent. 

" Very good ; it interferes, the gratification of 
it would interfere fatally, with the ambition of 
each of us. Our ambitions are odious, but we 
are tied fast to them." 

" Ah, why ain t we simple ? " Miriam quavered. 



686  

" Why ain t we of the people comme tout le 
monde just a man and a girl liking each 
