tant. Dear me, why do you like us so much ? " 

" Like you ? I loathe you ! " 

" Je le vois parbleu bien ! I mean, why do you 
feel us, judge us, understand us so well ? I please 
you because you see, because you know ; and be 
cause I please you, you must adapt me to your 
convenience, you must take me over, as they say. 
You admire me as an artist, and therefore you 
wish to put me into a box in which the artist will 
breathe her last. Ah, be reasonable ; you must 
let her live ! " 

" Let her live ? As if I could prevent her liv 
ing ! " Peter cried, with unmistakable conviction. 
