"Dying to sit?" repeated Nick, whose turn 
it was, this time, to feel his color rise. 

"Any time you like, after Easter, when she 
comes up to town. She wants a full-length, and 
your very best, your most splendid work." 

Nick stared, not caring that he had blushed. 
" Is she serious ? " 

" Ah, Nick serious ! " Biddy reasoned ten 
derly. She came nearer to him, and he thought 



 86 1 

she was going to weep again. He took her by 
